### Key design decisions

**`db_utils.py`** — `.env` is loaded relative to the script file path, so `uv run` works correctly from either the repo root or inside `data_pipeline/`. Connection pool is pre-pinged to prevent stale-connection failures.

**`ingest_api.py`** — A single `_http_get()` helper with configurable retry/backoff is shared by all three HTTP-based ingestors. Polygon uses the official `polygon-api-client` library and enforces exactly `time.sleep(12)` between tickers. DSO is computed as a proxy using liquid current assets when a direct accounts-receivable field is absent.

**`ingest_agent.py`** — `ShipmentRecord` has 21 typed fields with three Pydantic validators that strip currency symbols, thousand-separator commas, and trailing unit tokens from numeric fields. The `format=ShipmentBatch.model_json_schema()` parameter hands the full JSON Schema directly to Ollama's constrained-decoding layer, guaranteeing parseable output even from smaller models. A `_check_ollama_available()` pre-flight function verifies the daemon is up and the model is pulled before launching the browser.

**`clean_data.py`** — The `audit_nulls()` pass runs first and records which columns will be dropped vs. imputed, so both Stage 1 and Stage 2 operate from the same pre-computed statistics. Indicator columns are inserted using `df.insert(get_loc(col) + 1, ...)` which always resolves the correct post-insertion position by name, not index, making the insertion loop numerically safe.

